  "contentHtml": "<h1>What is RAM?</h1>\n<p>We want to store data structures in a computer component called random access memory.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Referred to as <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation>RAM</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">R</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">M</span></span></span></span> for short.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Arrays are ordered and contiguous.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mo>[</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>]</mo></mrow><annotation>[1, 2, 3]</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mclose\">]</span></span></span></span></li>\n<li>Understood in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>b</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation>bits</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">bi</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span></span></span></span> (1s and 0s).</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Bytes and Bits</h2>\n<p>One single <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>b</mi><mi>y</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow><annotation>byte</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">b</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">y</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span></span></span></span> is made up of 8 bits.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>In the modern day, we think in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>g</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>g</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mi>y</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation>gigabytes</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">g</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">g</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ab</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">y</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">es</span></span></span></span> <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>G</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><annotation>(GB)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">GB</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mi>y</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation>terrabytes</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">err</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ab</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">y</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">es</span></span></span></span> <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>T</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><annotation>(TB)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">TB</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The most common data type, the <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>g</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow><annotation>integer</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">in</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">g</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">er</span></span></span></span> is stored in 4 bytes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>32 bits of memory.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Addresses and Values</h2>\n<p>For each data type, a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation>address</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">dd</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ress</span></span></span></span> and a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>v</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>l</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow><annotation>value</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">v</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">u</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span></span></span></span> are assigned.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>An address is a distinct location in memory.</li>\n<li>A value represents the data type.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The value can be of any data type.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><annotation>string</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">r</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">in</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">g</span></span></span></span>, for example.\n<ul>\n<li>Or an <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><annotation>array</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">rr</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">y</span></span></span></span></li>\n<li>Or a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>b</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>l</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi></mrow><annotation>boolean</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">b</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">oo</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">an</span></span></span></span></li>\n<li>Any other data type.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Integers and strings are separated by 4 bytes, or 32 bits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Address denoted with a $ sign.\n<ul>\n<li>Followed by the amount of bytes.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"/dsa/ram/RAM.png\" alt=\"Image\"></p>",
